[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_0000482
name: Surface irrigation iron oxyhydroxide concentration
def: "The concentration of FeOH3 (iron oxyhydroxide) in the water used for surface irrigation. This parameter is relevant for Earth system modeling as it influences the availability of iron in the soil and its subsequent impact on plant growth and nutrient cycling. The concentration of FeOH3 can vary depending on factors such as soil properties, water quality, and agricultural practices." []
comment: Definition source - Claude Sonnet 4 through GitHub Copilot in VSCode (Sep 25 2025)
