[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_0000485
name: Surface irrigation calcium hydroxide concentration
def: "The concentration of calcium hydroxide (CaOH) in the water used for surface irrigation. It is a parameter that affects the quality of the irrigation water and can have an impact on soil pH and nutrient availability for plants. The CaOH concentration is typically measured in units of mass per volume (e.g., mg/L) and is an important parameter to consider when assessing the potential effects of irrigation water on crop growth and soil chemistry." []
