property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_0001397
name: Atmospheric methane concentration
def: "The abundance of methane (CH4) gas in the Earth's atmosphere. It is expressed as the volume of CH4 per unit volume of air (parts per million, ppm) or as a mixing ratio. Methane is an important greenhouse gas and contributes to climate change. Monitoring and understanding changes in atmospheric CH4 concentration is crucial for climate models and Earth system simulations." []
comment: ClimForcDataType.txt
synonym: "CH4E_col" RELATED []
