property_value: bervo:BERVO_measurement_of bervo:BERVO_8000024
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_0001398
name: Atmospheric hydrogen gas concentration
def: "The amount of hydrogen gas (H2) in the Earth's atmosphere, expressed typically in parts per million by volume (ppmv). Measuring this concentration is important in understanding the Earth's climate system, as H2 is one of the major constituent gases in the Earth's atmosphere and plays a critical role in various atmospheric processes." []
comment: ClimForcDataType.txt
synonym: "H2GE_col" RELATED []
