[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000298
name: Experimental context
def: "Metadata that describes the overall design, setup, and conditions of an experimental system. This includes information about the rationale, hypotheses, and organizational structure of the experiment, essential for understanding the scientific context and reproducibility of research findings." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
