property_value: bervo:BERVO_measured_in http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_measurement_of http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000301
name: Replicate series
def: "Multiple independent measurements or samples collected under identical or nearly identical conditions to assess measurement variability, reproducibility, and statistical robustness. Replicates include biological replicates (different organisms or samples) and technical replicates (repeated measurements on same sample), both critical for quantifying experimental uncertainty and establishing confidence in results." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000005
