property_value: bervo:BERVO_measurement_of http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000307
name: Anaerobic
def: "Environmental or metabolic conditions characterized by the absence or near-absence of dissolved oxygen. Anaerobic processes are prevalent in waterlogged soils, sediments, and water bodies, driving anaerobic respiration, methanogenesis, and other biochemical transformations critical to biogeochemical cycling in anoxic environments." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000015
is_a: bervo:BERVO_8000232 ! Concept
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Attribute http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Context http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_has_unit "NA" xsd:string
property_value: bervo:BERVO_measured_in http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_measurement_of http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000308
name: Aerobic
def: "Environmental or metabolic conditions in which dissolved oxygen is present at concentrations sufficient to support aerobic respiration and oxidative metabolic pathways. Aerobic conditions predominate in well-drained soils, water column surface layers, and are generally favorable for rapid organic matter decomposition and energy availability in ecosystems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000016
