property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000316
name: Bead size
def: "The physical diameter or volume specifications of beads employed in soil or tissue homogenization and chemical extraction procedures. Bead size directly influences grinding efficiency, shear forces, and the uniformity of particle size distribution in processed samples." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000031
