property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000317
name: Delta-H
def: "The change in enthalpy (ΔH) representing the heat energy absorbed or released during a chemical reaction at constant pressure. Delta-H is fundamental for assessing reaction spontaneity, thermodynamic feasibility, and energy requirements in biogeochemical processes and environmental chemistry applications." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
synonym: "deltaH" EXACT []
synonym: "ΔH" EXACT []
