[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000318
name: Specific activity
def: "The catalytic activity of an enzyme normalized to protein mass, expressed as units of product formed per unit time per unit protein. Specific activity quantifies enzyme efficiency and purity, enabling standardization of enzyme measurements and comparison of catalytic performance across different protein preparations." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
