property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000320
name: Physicochemical state
def: "A descriptor of the physical and chemical status of matter including phase (solid, liquid, gas), solubility state, sorption status, or location within environmental compartments. This concept specifies whether substances are dissolved, suspended, sorbed, or present in particular environmental matrices, affecting their bioavailability and environmental fate." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
