property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000321
name: Detection limit
def: "The minimum concentration, mass, or signal intensity that can be reliably distinguished from background noise by an analytical instrument or method. Detection limits define the lower boundary of quantitative measurement ranges and are critical for data quality assessment and comparison of analytical capabilities." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000038
