property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000322
name: Biological context
def: "Information describing the biological setting, organismal status, population characteristics, or ecological relationships relevant to a measurement or observation. Biological context includes organism identity, life stage, metabolic state, and ecological role, essential for interpreting biological and biogeochemical data." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
