[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000323
name: Microbial strain
def: "A genetically distinct population of microorganisms identified by strain designation, culture collection number, or isolate designation. Microbial strain specification is essential for reproducibility of microbiological research and enables tracking of specific phenotypic or genotypic characteristics across experiments." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
