property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000328
name: Nitrogen source
def: "The compound or element used as a nitrogen supply for microbial or plant growth, including inorganic forms (nitrate, ammonium) and organic forms (amino acids, proteins). Nitrogen source type influences microbial community composition and metabolic pathways in biogeochemical cycling." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
