property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000329
name: Electron donor
def: "The reduced chemical compound that serves as the primary energy source for microbial oxidative metabolism and growth, such as hydrogen, sulfide, iron(II), or organic matter. Electron donor identity determines the thermodynamic driving force and metabolic type of microorganisms in environmental systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000057
