property_value: bervo:BERVO_measurement_of http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000330
name: Electron acceptor
def: "The oxidized chemical species that serves as the terminal electron acceptor in microbial respiration, including oxygen, nitrate, sulfate, iron(III), and other inorganic compounds. Electron acceptor availability determines the thermodynamic favorability and type of respiration (aerobic, anaerobic) in biogeochemical systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000058
