property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000332
name: Gene GI
def: "The GenBank identifier (GI number) serving as a unique accession reference for specific gene sequences in public databases. GI numbers enable unambiguous linking of experimental data to specific genetic sequences and facilitate bioinformatic analyses." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
