property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000335
name: TIGR role
def: "A functional classification system from The Institute for Genomic Research (TIGR) that assigns functional roles to proteins based on sequence homology and structural similarities. TIGR roles enable systematic functional annotation and comparative metabolic analysis across microbial genomes." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
