property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000336
name: Pfam domain accession
def: "The unique identifier for protein domain families in the Pfam database representing evolutionarily related protein domains with conserved structures and functions. Pfam domain accessions enable identification of functional motifs and comparative protein evolution analysis." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
synonym: "pfam ID" EXACT []
