property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000337
name: Growth rate
def: "The increase in organism biomass, cell number, or population size per unit time, quantifying the speed of biological growth under specific conditions. Growth rate measurements are fundamental for assessing organism fitness, evaluating culture performance, and determining population dynamics in microbial and ecological studies." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000079
