property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000338
name: Doubling time
def: "The time interval required for a population to double in size during exponential growth phase. Doubling time is a key parameter characterizing organism growth rate and is essential for assessing growth kinetics and comparing growth performance under different conditions." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000080
