property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000339
name: Time since inoculation
def: "The elapsed time interval from introduction of organisms into culture media until the time of sampling or measurement. Time since inoculation is essential for relating growth measurements to the exponential, stationary, or death phases of microbial growth curves." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000081
