property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000342
name: Environmental sample
def: "A physical specimen collected from natural environments such as soils, waters, sediments, or organisms, representing a specific location and time. Environmental samples are fundamental for characterizing ecosystem conditions, tracking environmental changes, and conducting field-based biogeochemical research." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000100
