property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000344
name: Community assembly process
def: "The mechanisms and processes through which biological communities develop and stabilize over time, including colonization, competition, facilitation, and stochastic processes. Community assembly processes determine ecosystem structure, functional redundancy, and resilience to environmental disturbances." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
