property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000346
name: Sequencing technology
def: "The platform and methodology used for DNA or RNA sequencing, including next-generation sequencing (Illumina, PacBio, Nanopore) and traditional approaches. Sequencing technology selection critically affects read quality, read length, throughput, and cost of molecular analyses." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000116
