property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000348
name: Conductivity
def: "A measure of a material's ability to conduct electrical current, primarily determined by dissolved ion concentration and mobility. Conductivity is an important indicator of water quality, salinity, and total dissolved solids in aquatic and terrestrial systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000124
is_a: bervo:BERVO_8000232 ! Concept
property_value: bervo:BERVO_Attribute http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA
