property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000349
name: Redox potential
def: "The electron activity or oxidation-reduction potential of a solution, measured in millivolts, indicating the tendency of substances to be oxidized or reduced. Redox potential controls the solubility and bioavailability of elements and drives major biogeochemical transformations in environmental systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000125
is_a: bervo:BERVO_8000232 ! Concept
