[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000351
name: Hybridization intensity
def: "The signal strength or fluorescence intensity resulting from molecular hybridization between labeled probes and complementary sequences. Hybridization intensity measurements are fundamental for microarray analysis, enabling quantification of nucleic acid abundance and identification of genomic variations." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
