property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000353
name: Enzyme activity
def: "The catalytic efficiency of an enzyme measured as the rate of substrate conversion per unit enzyme or per unit time. Enzyme activity measurements quantify metabolic function and are critical for assessing organism capability to perform specific biogeochemical transformations." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
