property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000357
name: Binary
def: "A data format or classification system with two mutually exclusive states or categories (yes/no, present/absent, true/false). Binary representations enable efficient storage and analysis of presence-absence data and dichotomous properties in large datasets." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
