property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000366
name: P value
def: "The probability of observing test statistics as extreme as or more extreme than the observed value under the null hypothesis. P-values are fundamental for statistical hypothesis testing and determining significance of research findings." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000156
is_a: bervo:BERVO_8000244 ! Quantitative value
