property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000376
name: False negative
def: "An instance where a prediction or test incorrectly fails to identify the presence of a condition or feature when it is actually present. False negatives represent missed detections and affect sensitivity metrics." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
xref: COMO:0000167
