property_value: bervo:BERVO_Qualifier http://www.w3.org/2002/07/NA

[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000378
name: Pearson coefficient
def: "A parametric correlation coefficient measuring the linear relationship between two continuous variables, assuming normal distribution. Pearson correlation is widely used for assessing strength of linear association in statistical analysis." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
