[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000381
name: Goodman and Kruskal's gamma
def: "A measure of association for ordinal variables that quantifies agreement between two ordinal rankings, accounting for tied observations. Gamma ranges from -1 to +1 and is less affected by table marginals." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
