[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000384
name: Principal component
def: "A linear combination of original variables that captures maximum variance in multivariate data with minimal dimensionality. Principal components are orthogonal and ordered by descending variance." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
