[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000385
name: Operational Taxonomic Unit
def: "Operational Taxonomic Unit, a grouping of sequences within a specified sequence similarity threshold used in microbial community analysis. OTUs approximate species-level groups in 16S rRNA gene sequencing." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
synonym: "OTU" EXACT []
