[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000386
name: Amplicon Sequence Variant
def: "Amplicon Sequence Variant, an exact biological sequence variant identified in high-throughput sequencing that represents true molecular entities. ASVs offer higher resolution than OTUs for microbial community characterization." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
synonym: "ASV" EXACT []
