[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000388
name: Sequence type
def: "The classification or category of a nucleic acid or protein sequence such as DNA, RNA, or amino acid sequences. Sequence type designation specifies the chemical nature and interpretation of sequence data." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
