[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000442
name: Projected Coordinate System
def: "A coordinate reference system that uses a map projection to represent locations on a curved surface as planar coordinates, enabling positions to be expressed as easting and northing values in linear units. A projected coordinate system includes a base geographic coordinate system, projection method, datum, linear unit, and projection parameters; examples include UTM Zone 13N and State Plane zones." []
comment: Definition revised to generalize the previous State plane zone term to projected coordinate systems that can qualify easting and northing values.
xref: http://www.w3.org/2002/07/Class
