[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000471
name: Aphotic
def: "A region or layer of water or sediment that receives no sunlight, characteristic of deep ocean or lake environments below the photic zone. Aphotic environments support chemosynthetic and heterotrophic microbial communities." []
comment: Definition source - Claude 4.5 Sonnet through Claude Code in VSCode (Dec 16 2025)
