[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000537
name: Negative
def: "A qualifier indicating that the quantity represents a negative value or direction, often used to distinguish loss or removal processes from gain or addition processes. This directional qualifier is important for understanding bidirectional fluxes and net balances in biogeochemical systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude Sonnet 4 through GitHub Copilot in VSCode (Jan 8 2026)
