[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000542
name: Mineralization
def: "The biological breakdown of organic compounds into inorganic forms, converting organic nitrogen to ammonium, organic phosphorus to phosphate, and organic carbon to carbon dioxide. This attribute measures the rate of nutrient transformation from organic to plant-available inorganic forms in soils and aquatic systems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude Sonnet 4 through GitHub Copilot in VSCode (Jan 8 2026)
