[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000543
name: Absorptivity
def: "The capacity of a material to absorb radiation, heat, or substances, expressed as the fraction of incident energy or material absorbed. This attribute quantifies absorption efficiency in processes including solar radiation interception by vegetation and nutrient uptake by organisms." []
