[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000546
name: Primary productivity
def: "The rate at which energy is converted to organic matter through photosynthesis by primary producers, representing the fundamental energy input to ecosystems. This attribute measures the gross or net production of biomass by autotrophic organisms." []
