[Term]
id: bervo:BERVO_8000552
name: Litter layer
def: "The accumulation of dead plant material on the soil surface forming a distinct organic horizon that mediates decomposition and nutrient cycling. This layer provides habitat for decomposer organisms, regulates soil microclimate, and controls the release of nutrients from organic matter in forest and grassland ecosystems." []
comment: Definition source - Claude Sonnet 4 through GitHub Copilot in VSCode (Jan 8 2026)
